
[1]hair-breadth

   HA'IR-BREADTH, n. [See Breadth.] The diameter or breadth of a hair; a
   very small distance.

   --Seven hundred chosen men left-handed; every one could

   sling stones to a hair-breadth. Judges 20.

      It is used as an adjective; as a hair-breadth escape. But in New
                  England, it is generally hair's breadth.
